  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building &amp; Supporting Schools</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education in the Horn of Africa is critical to improving the livelihoods of millions of people. Current education-related programs aim to provide and maintain infrastructure so that students can benefit for years to come. ARAHA is especially focused on providing educational opportunities to IDPs and refugees across the Horn of Africa, who often lack access.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kassala City in Sudan is home to thousands of Eritrean refugees residing in refugee camps. Education opportunities are very limited due to scarce infrastructure. The Alhussain School is receiving furniture for its school building, providing desks, tables, chairs, etc. for students and teachers. 

Alnidal School, also located in Kassala City, educates 400 Eritrean refugee children each year. In order to keep the school running, ARAHA is covering rent expenses for the year.

ARAHA is funding the construction of 4 classrooms at Lower Juba University to house a nursing school. Students will receive technical and practical training necessary for successful nursing career.</narrative>
  </description>
